issuesFound.explanation:
inlineValidator.bind() creates an error element and marks the field as invalid with CSS classes, but it never adds aria‑invalid="true" when validation fails. This violates WCAG 2.1 (ARIA state must reflect validation status).  
Fix (inside the if (!result.valid) branch):  
```js
if (!result.valid) {
  srUtils.markInvalid(field, errorEl);
  setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'true');   // ← add this line
}
```  

