issuesFound.explanation:
When the email fails validation the script only adds an error message; it never marks the `<input>` with `aria-invalid="true"`, so screen readers do not hear the error.  
  Fix (add to the validation branch):  
```js
if (!result.valid) {
  setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'true');   // announce error
  // existing error‑message handling …
}
```
  Also clear on success: `removeAttribute(field, 'aria-invalid');`

The badge shows the number of matching products but no live‑region is used, so users of assistive tech are unaware when the result set changes.  
  Fix (add a hidden live region and update it):  
```js
// in init()
const _countLive = createElement('div', {
  id: 'product-count-live',
  role: 'status',
  'aria-live': 'polite',
  class: 'sr-only',
});
document.body.appendChild(_countLive);

// replace _updateCountBadge
function _updateCountBadge(count) {
  _countBadge.textContent = String(count);
  _countLive.textContent = `${count} product${count!==1?'s':''} found`;
}
```

When the user switches between monthly/annual pricing the UI updates numbers but no ARIA live region is used, leaving screen‑reader users unaware of the change.  
  Fix (add a live region and announce):  
```js
// create once (e.g., in pricing.init)
const _priceLive = createElement('div', {
  id: 'price-change-live',
  role: 'status',
  'aria-live': 'polite',
  class: 'sr-only',
});
document.body.appendChild(_priceLive);

// inside setPeriod after updating cards
_priceLive.textContent = `Pricing switched to ${BILLING_PERIODS[period].label} billing`;
```

